This article is a letter from President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President Pro Tempore of the Senate. The letter provides a supplemental consolidated report on military operations conducted by the United States in support of counterterrorism efforts. The report mentions deployments of U.S. combat-equipped forces in various locations around the world to enhance counterterrorism capabilities and support operations of allies and partners. The letter also provides specific information about counterterrorism deployments in select countries such as Afghanistan, Somalia, Yemen, Cuba, Niger, and Chad. It mentions the ongoing efforts to combat al-Qa'ida, the Taliban, and associated forces, as well as efforts to locate schoolgirls kidnapped in Nigeria and address the threat posed by the Lord's Resistance Army. The letter also mentions military operations in Egypt, Jordan, Kosovo, Libya, Yemen, and South Sudan. Overall, the letter emphasizes the efforts of the United States to combat terrorism and protect U.S. citizens and interests.